WEBVTT

05:16.818 --> 05:18.653
Taylor!
Tangina.

05:18.736 --> 05:20.071
Over here!

05:23.074 --> 05:25.827
I think we finally
found the core.

05:26.327 --> 05:28.579
We dug under the swimming pool.

05:29.330 --> 05:32.375
This is directly below
the old graveyard.

05:32.917 --> 05:34.836
There's a presence.

06:17.336 --> 06:19.755
There's
something terrible.

06:19.839 --> 06:21.382
Too much power.

07:38.209 --> 07:41.128
I've seen it in dreams.

07:41.796 --> 07:43.172
What is it?

07:45.758 --> 07:47.677
Where's the family now?

07:53.224 --> 07:54.266
Did you make that?

07:54.350 --> 07:55.851
It's like
an inch and a half.

07:55.935 --> 07:56.978
Let me try this up
against her arm.

07:57.061 --> 07:59.021
Oh, Mother, it's too
hot on the kids.

07:59.105 --> 08:00.815
- Oh, Dad.
- Okay. Ready.

08:04.151 --> 08:06.445
You'll be lucky if your
teeth don't fall out from that.

08:08.197 --> 08:10.366
Did you think up that
sandwich all by yourself?

08:10.449 --> 08:11.867
No. Gramma helped.

08:11.951 --> 08:15.287
What a fib! Grab me the red yarn
out of my basket, will you, honey?

08:17.081 --> 08:18.374
E. Buzz, stop!

08:18.457 --> 08:19.792
That's disgusting.

08:19.875 --> 08:21.669
- Oh, Rob!
- E. Buzz.

08:21.794 --> 08:23.087
E. Buzz, down!

08:23.129 --> 08:25.506
Well, maybe E.
Buzz would like some mustard.

08:25.589 --> 08:28.217
E. Buzz,
get down. Down, E. Buzz.

08:28.926 --> 08:30.636
I'll say "down," and then
he'll get down. Down!

08:32.763 --> 08:33.764
He really listens to you.

08:33.847 --> 08:36.767
Honey, now could you
get me the yellow yarn?

08:37.476 --> 08:40.270
Oh, Rob, very nice
to share with E. Buzz.

08:40.354 --> 08:42.231
E. Buzz knows
how to share with Robbie.

08:42.313 --> 08:44.358
E. Buzz,
get down.

08:46.110 --> 08:47.570
Thank you, angel.

08:47.653 --> 08:49.363
Come on, Guerrero!
Hit it out of the park!

08:49.447 --> 08:50.573
Yeah, hit it!

08:50.656 --> 08:52.283
<i>Guerrero has fired
a right and struck out...</i>

08:54.452 --> 08:56.912
Dad, can't we get a TV
like everybody else?

08:56.996 --> 08:59.123
No, no, we can't get a TV.

08:59.540 --> 09:02.334
Great, I'll just have
to grow up retarded.

09:02.418 --> 09:05.296
Come on, Rob, kids
don't grow up retardo

09:05.379 --> 09:06.464
because of lack of television.

09:06.547 --> 09:07.715
<i>Guerrero drives one
to left center field...</i>

09:07.798 --> 09:10.885
Atta boy, Guerrero! Did
you see that, Robbie?

09:10.968 --> 09:13.220
No, Dad.
I didn't see it.

09:13.971 --> 09:16.474
Well, you gotta use
your imagination, son.

09:17.183 --> 09:19.602
Come on. We're gonna
test this baby out.

09:20.144 --> 09:21.187
God!

09:28.194 --> 09:31.614
How am I gonna sell this to
innocent housewives, Robbie?

09:31.697 --> 09:33.157
I don't know, Dad.

09:55.346 --> 09:57.223
Whatcha drawing, honey?

09:57.598 --> 09:59.517
Don't know. Stuff.

10:00.434 --> 10:02.186
You draw very well.

10:03.395 --> 10:05.898
Do you want to be an
artist when you grow up?

10:05.981 --> 10:08.692
Maybe. Don't want
to grow up much.

10:12.029 --> 10:13.280
How come?

10:13.364 --> 10:15.116
Probably not much fun.

10:15.199 --> 10:16.742
Oh, sure it is.

10:17.535 --> 10:19.787
I've loved every age I've been.

10:20.371 --> 10:22.540
They all have their blessings.

10:22.915 --> 10:24.708
When I was your age,

10:25.543 --> 10:29.171
I learned that I could do things
that other folks couldn't.

10:29.713 --> 10:31.715
Like what kind of things?

10:33.217 --> 10:35.719
I just knew things.

10:36.554 --> 10:39.265
I didn't know how
I knew, but I did.

10:40.099 --> 10:41.433
Like what?

10:44.019 --> 10:48.983
Once, my mother lost her bracelet
and I knew where it was.

10:50.151 --> 10:53.696
Two miles from our house in a
place that I'd never been.

10:54.446 --> 10:55.531
Now,

10:56.824 --> 11:00.870
do you ever know things
and can't explain why?

11:07.585 --> 11:08.627
Yes?

11:09.253 --> 11:10.337
Yes.

11:12.173 --> 11:13.674
Well, darling,

11:14.550 --> 11:18.137
that's a very special gift
that you and I have.

11:19.388 --> 11:21.473
It's nothing to be scared of.

11:21.557 --> 11:23.767
Will it help me be a ballerina?

11:23.851 --> 11:25.519
Yes, sure it will.

11:26.103 --> 11:28.355
Whatever you dream, you can be.

11:32.067 --> 11:33.569
They denied
our claim again!

11:33.652 --> 11:34.695
What?

11:34.778 --> 11:38.032
I told you, we never should have told them
that the house vanished into thin air.

11:38.115 --> 11:39.783
That's exactly what
I've been talking about.

11:39.867 --> 11:42.453
You tell the truth, and
what do you get? Nada!

11:42.536 --> 11:43.954
They say that if
the house disappeared,

11:44.038 --> 11:45.748
then technically,
it's only missing.

11:45.831 --> 11:47.082
Missing?

11:47.333 --> 11:50.127
What do they think, this house
is going to return or something?

11:50.211 --> 11:52.421
Now, it's been a full year.
The house is not coming back.

11:52.504 --> 11:55.466
I got a gut feeling, Diane,
I'm positive about that.

11:55.549 --> 11:57.301
I know that, Steven.

11:58.010 --> 11:59.553
You tell them that...

11:59.637 --> 12:02.556
No, no, I'm gonna fill
out the fourth claim.

12:02.765 --> 12:04.516
Okay, what are we going
to claim this time?

12:04.600 --> 12:06.602
Act of God? Housenapping?

12:07.311 --> 12:10.189
Steven, we are almost broke.

12:10.272 --> 12:13.067
Okay, we're broke,
but we're not starving.

12:13.317 --> 12:16.987
Okay, but I don't happen to like
having to live off my mother.

12:17.071 --> 12:20.157
And I think that we deserve a
house of our own again someday.

12:20.241 --> 12:22.034
Oh, honey, gee, gosh.

12:22.368 --> 12:24.203
See, that's the difference
between you and me, Diane,

12:24.286 --> 12:25.913
I am into downward mobility.

12:25.996 --> 12:28.499
I'm not settled for it,
I'm into it.

12:28.999 --> 12:30.918
I like getting out there in the
streets and meeting those...

12:31.001 --> 12:32.336
