We can't just drive around.

30:26.034 --> 30:29.579
Well, Mother, just don't you
bring him over to my house.

30:29.662 --> 30:31.247
Waitress, check!

30:40.089 --> 30:44.093
Listen,
children, you can't run from this thing.

30:44.177 --> 30:46.888
It has made contact
and will stop at nothing.

30:46.971 --> 30:49.349
You've got to fight it head on.

30:49.432 --> 30:50.933
Stay together.

30:51.559 --> 30:52.727
Be loving.

30:53.311 --> 30:54.604
Be brave.

30:56.272 --> 30:57.398
Mama?

31:02.904 --> 31:03.988
Mama?

31:05.698 --> 31:07.158
I'm not your mother, lady.

31:07.241 --> 31:08.659
Elizabeth, are you okay?

31:08.743 --> 31:10.244
What happened?

31:10.787 --> 31:13.289
- What happened?
- You went funny.

31:16.793 --> 31:19.045
But it sounded like her.
I don't understand.

31:19.128 --> 31:21.255
Honey, you can't
explain stuff like that.

31:21.339 --> 31:24.425
It just happens. I mean,
there's no reason for it.

31:24.509 --> 31:25.510
What are
you talking about?

31:25.593 --> 31:27.887
It doesn't
matter, honey.

31:29.639 --> 31:30.890
What do
you want?

31:30.973 --> 31:32.475
She told you the truth.

31:32.558 --> 31:33.935
Who?

31:35.269 --> 31:37.105
You mean that...

31:37.188 --> 31:39.607
Ah, man, are you in cahoots
with the lady in there?

31:40.733 --> 31:42.527
I cahoot with no one.

31:42.902 --> 31:44.904
Then why are you following us?

31:44.987 --> 31:46.531
I came to help.

31:47.657 --> 31:49.534
Oh, God. I mean,
you don't understand.

31:49.617 --> 31:51.327
See, we don't want your help.

31:51.411 --> 31:52.954
We don't want anybody's help.

31:53.037 --> 31:54.997
We want to be left alone!

31:55.081 --> 31:57.667
Steven, wait.
Why did Tangina send you?

31:57.750 --> 31:59.419
Why didn't she come herself?

32:00.878 --> 32:02.380
It's my kind of job.

32:02.797 --> 32:03.965
You know, maybe
it's no coincidence.

32:04.048 --> 32:07.260
This guy shows up,
things go kinda screwy.

32:07.677 --> 32:09.178
Get off my car!

32:14.392 --> 32:16.269
Get in the car, Diane.

32:17.186 --> 32:19.647
Get in the car, kids.
Diane, get in the car.

32:19.730 --> 32:22.150
Steven, wait a minute. Steven,
let's listen to the man.

32:22.233 --> 32:24.777
Fine, you listen to him.
I wanna go home.

32:24.861 --> 32:26.946
Listen, let's be
sensible about this.

32:27.029 --> 32:29.615
Sensible? What is sensible, honey?
Nobody can help us.

32:29.699 --> 32:32.618
Now, let's just get in the car
and get the hell out of here!

32:32.702 --> 32:34.662
And go where?
It followed us here.

32:34.745 --> 32:37.290
It'll follow us wherever we go.
We can't just keep running.

32:37.373 --> 32:38.624
Where are you from?

32:38.708 --> 32:40.334
I'm from
all over.

32:40.418 --> 32:42.044
This is Katrina.

32:42.253 --> 32:43.337
Katrina?
Mmm-hmm.

32:43.421 --> 32:44.839
Hi, Katrina.

32:45.131 --> 32:46.507
What's that?

32:46.591 --> 32:48.384
It's my medicine bag.

32:49.552 --> 32:50.720
Charms.

32:51.637 --> 32:52.722
See?

33:02.523 --> 33:04.734
The house is okay?
You're sure?

33:04.942 --> 33:07.361
E. Buzz agrees.
It's okay for now.

33:13.075 --> 33:16.078
Oh, the dog agrees, huh? Gee,
that's terrific, isn't it?

33:16.162 --> 33:17.246
Yes.

33:19.123 --> 33:20.416
Your car.

33:23.169 --> 33:24.629
STEVEN; Yeah?

33:26.923 --> 33:28.299
Very angry-

33:29.842 --> 33:31.052
Uh-huh.

33:31.928 --> 33:33.304
I'll fix it.

33:34.305 --> 33:35.723
Make it happy?

33:43.981 --> 33:45.107
Okay.

33:58.955 --> 34:01.457
I've read about these
rain dances. I know.

34:01.541 --> 34:02.542
I understand,
Tangina.

34:02.625 --> 34:04.377
We don't need rain.

34:04.877 --> 34:07.797
I can't say that
Steven fully trusts him yet.

34:08.047 --> 34:10.299
Well, you can't
blame him, I mean...

34:10.382 --> 34:13.511
Yeah, okay. Well, thanks, Tangina.
We will. Bye.

34:19.183 --> 34:22.562
Honey, she says he's okay. I think
we should give him a chance.

34:22.645 --> 34:23.728
Tangina says he's okay?

34:23.813 --> 34:24.981
Yeah.

34:25.313 --> 34:26.357
Oh, that's great.

34:26.440 --> 34:27.650
Keep an open mind, Steven.

34:29.569 --> 34:32.196
Diane, I mean, really.
This is bizarre.

34:33.155 --> 34:36.033
You know, look, I've got
nothing against these people.

34:36.117 --> 34:39.411
You <i>know,</i> I <i>mean,</i> I read
<i>Bury My Heart at Wounded Knee.</i>

34:39.495 --> 34:41.539
I got through most
of the chapters.

34:41.621 --> 34:43.373
I got some Indian
in me, I think.

34:43.456 --> 34:46.377
A sixteenth, my mother
will never admit to it.

34:46.460 --> 34:49.045
But honey, I mean,
what if this guy

34:49.672 --> 34:52.592
is, like, an escapee
from the tribal asylum?

34:54.342 --> 34:56.596
Mom,
come look at this!

35:02.184 --> 35:03.811
Oh, my God!

35:08.858 --> 35:10.568
I don't believe it!

35:39.764 --> 35:40.973
What are you doing?

35:41.057 --> 35:43.309
Oh, hi, Mom. I'm going to
help protect the family now.

35:43.392 --> 35:44.727
Let me see.

35:46.520 --> 35:48.439
Come outside, Robbie.
Hey, I'm a big guy now.

35:48.522 --> 35:50.733
And I'm still your mother. Go
in the house and wait for me.

35:50.816 --> 35:52.234
Thanks, Mom.

35:53.861 --> 35:55.696
He wants to be a man.

35:55.780 --> 35:57.156
Well, there are a lot
of ways to be a man.

35:57.239 --> 36:00.951
I'm not sure wearing claw marks
and war paint is one of them.

36:01.035 --> 36:02.745
How would you know?

36:04.747 --> 36:05.831
What?

36:08.000 --> 36:10.044
You're not a man, are you?

36:11.253 --> 36:14.215
Okay, I'm not a man.
But you're not a mother!

36:15.007 --> 36:16.884
It is my job to do
everything I can

36:16.967 --> 36:19.679
to make my children
part of a normal world.

36:19.762 --> 36:22.682
A world of school,
and friends, and lovers,

36:22.765 --> 36:25.226
and families of
their own, someday.

36:25.685 --> 36:27.353
Well, that's good.

36:29.146 --> 36:30.648
Right, I know.

36:32.316 --> 36:34.694
And I hope that they'll learn
to forget all this soon.

36:34.777 --> 36:37.196
They cannot learn by forgetting.

36:37.279 --> 36:38.489
Well, what would you have me do,

36:38.572 --> 36:40.783
I mean, they're just
children, for God's sake.

36:40.866 --> 36:44.036
Children have fought wars.
They've built nations.

36:44.453 --> 36:46.789
They are strong
and have courage.

36:47.415 --> 36:50.126
Don't treat them any less than
that because they're young.

36:59.969 --> 37:01.470
Taylor!

37:02.138 --> 37:03.389
Taylor!

37:04.932 --> 37:06.142
Taylor!

37:06.684 --> 37:08.436
Okay, Taylor, okay.

37:08.936 --> 37:10.855
Okay, huh? Huh? Okay.

37:11.355 --> 37:12.898
You can stay in the house, okay?

37:12.982 --> 37:15.484
You can have my aura, my spirits,
the ghosts, the whole deal.

37:15.568 --> 37:18.696
The whole cazaba! But keep
your hands off my car!

37:18.988 --> 37:21.949
Okay? Hands off! It's
worse than it was before.

37:22.032 --> 37:23.409
Car's still angry, huh?

37:23.492 --> 37:25.995
Angry? That car
is pissed!

37:38.507 --> 37:43.804
<i>God is in his holy temple</i>

37:44.555 --> 37:48.851
<i>Earthly thoughts be silent now</i>

37:50.436 --> 37:55.733
<i>While with</i> reverence we assemble

37:55.858 --> 38:00.613
<i>And before his presence bow</i>

38:01.614 --> 38:03.824
Come on,
Carol Anne. It's raining!

38:03.908 --> 38:05.910
Come on! What's wrong?

38:06.368 --> 38:09.955
<i>He is with us now and ever</i>

38:10.039 --> 38:11.916
Carol Anne, come on!
Let's go.

38:11.999 --> 38:13.375
Mom, Dad!

38:13.501 --> 38:16.170
<i>As we call upon his name</i>

38:17.505 --> 38:22.593
<i>Aiding every good endeavor</i>

38:23.302 --> 38:25.638
<i>Guiding upward every aim</i>

38:25.721 --> 38:29.141
Honey, come inside.
You're getting soaked!

38:30.059 --> 38:31.685
Come on, sweetie.

38:40.194 --> 38:41.821
Can we help you?

38:41.904 --> 38:43.989
Haven't I seen you
somewhere before?

38:44.073 --> 38:45.741
That is possible!

38:46.075 --> 38:48.869
I get around.
I love getting around.

38:49.495 --> 38:51.580
Love talking to people.

38:52.248 --> 38:53.999
Even on a rainy day.

39:01.423 --> 39:03.133
Ha! Dog's shedding.

39:04.927 --> 39:06.095
Hi!

39:06.929 --> 39:07.972
Hi.

39:08.055 --> 39:09.807
I saw you at the shopping mall.

39:09.890 --> 39:14.311
Sure you did. I remember
your little angel, here.

39:14.687 --> 39:17.022
Allow me to introduce myself.

39:17.398 --> 39:18.774
Henry Kane.

39:20.442 --> 39:21.485
Mom!

39:22.111 --> 39:23.737
You know, I got to tell
you, we've had, uh...

39:23.821 --> 39:26.448
We've had enough of door-to-door
salesmen, if you don't mind.

39:26.532 --> 39:28.033
Reverend Kane!

39:28.617 --> 39:30.828
What I sell is free!

39:31.453 --> 39:34.290
Mind if I come in and
talk to you about it?

39:34.832 --> 39:37.167
Mom, I don't feel well.

39:38.127 --> 39:39.169
You know, I gotta...

39:39.253 --> 39:41.714
Maybe, we'll just talk
from here, all right?

39:41.797 --> 39:43.883
Come inside, baby. I
want to take your temperature.

39:43.966 --> 39:45.593
Come on, Robbie.

39:57.313 --> 40:00.024
I'm glad we have this
opportunity to talk

40:00.441 --> 40:02.735
with your family out of the way.

40:03.152 --> 40:07.156
Because I believe you
have a problem here.

40:08.115 --> 40:09.158
Oh, yeah?

40:09.241 --> 40:10.326
Yeah.

40:11.201 --> 40:15.247
I believe, there's an Indian
living here with you?

40:17.166 --> 40:18.334
Taylor.

40:19.585 --> 40:22.796
So that's what
he calls himself now.

40:25.382 --> 40:27.051
You are in danger!

40:27.718 --> 40:29.345
What do you mean?

40:29.678 --> 40:35.059
I'm with an organization whose
concern is families like your own,

40:35.851 --> 40:40.773
families in crisis that are
preyed upon by charlatans

40:40.856 --> 40:43.400
with fake magic
and false solutions!

40:43.734 --> 40:46.445
Now, I don't expect
you to believe me now,

40:46.528 --> 40:49.531
but let me come in and
talk to you about it.

40:50.699 --> 40:53.410
I don't know. This is just crazy.
This is nuts.

40:54.078 --> 40:59.541
Please! Open your heart and
your mind to what I'm saying.

41:00.459 --> 41:02.753
He is dangerous!

41:30.656 --> 41:35.285
I can see that he has a
strong hold on this family.

41:36.245 --> 41:41.333
Who do your wife and children
turn to with their problems?

41:43.043 --> 41:44.670
They turn to him.

41:45.379 --> 41:47.006
Now, don't they?

41:47.089 --> 41:49.842
They don't trust you

41:51.051 --> 41:52.261
anymore.

41:52.803 --> 41:54.430
What you fear

41:56.598 --> 42:00.602
is that you're not man enough

42:01.770 --> 42:06.108
to hold this family together.

42:08.652 --> 42:10.863
HOW do you know?

42:11.071 --> 42:12.406
Because,

42:13.866 --> 42:15.367
I'm smart.

42:18.370 --> 42:20.122
And I'm your friend.

42:22.666 --> 42:27.546
And I know what
you are thinking.

42:30.632 --> 42:31.717
How?

42:32.426 --> 42:33.469
Now,

42:34.636 --> 42:35.971
let me in.

42:37.347 --> 42:39.308
And let's talk about it.

42:43.437 --> 42:45.606
Let me in!

42:47.191 --> 42:48.859
You're my friend?

42:50.319 --> 42:52.738
Let me in!

42:55.491 --> 42:57.159
CAROL ANNE; Daddy?

42:59.870 --> 43:02.790
Now! Before it's too late!

43:06.627 --> 43:07.669
No.

43:07.961 --> 43:11.632
You're gonna die in there!
All of you!

43:11.882 --> 43:14.843
You are gonna die!

43:15.469 --> 43:17.471
Get the hell out of here!

43:23.519 --> 43:25.020
Sorry to see

43:26.105 --> 43:28.273
you're still unconvinced.

43:37.449 --> 43:39.660
A pleasure visiting with you.

43:40.869 --> 43:45.707
<i>As we call upon his name</i>

43:47.209 --> 43:52.339
<i>Aiding every good endeavor</i>

43:52.965 --> 43:58.387
<i>Guiding upward every aim</i>

44:17.281 --> 44:18.740
You did good.

44:20.409 --> 44:22.077
Who was that?

44:23.871 --> 44:25.664
That was him.

44:27.833 --> 44:28.917
Him?

44:31.920 --> 44:34.006
What are you talking about?

44:34.506 --> 44:36.550
He was testing your power.

44:38.385 --> 44:41.096
He comes in many forms,
but that was him.

44:46.018 --> 44:49.271
Now you're hooked. You're
on the path of a warrior.

44:49.897 --> 44:53.275
Hooked? Hey, wait. Taylor,
what are you talking about?

44:53.775 --> 44:57.112
Your confrontation with him
was a drain on your power.

44:57.571 --> 45:00.282
We don't have much time.
We must prepare.

45:01.450 --> 45:02.701
Prepare?

45:05.412 --> 45:06.622
Oh, God.

45:24.056 --> 45:25.724
Tequila.
Ta kill ya!

45:26.308 --> 45:27.851
You want a hit?

45:28.560 --> 45:31.313
No. I used to drink.
I had to give it up.

45:32.397 --> 45:33.482
Bad dreams.

45:33.649 --> 45:34.733
Mmm.

45:37.819 --> 45:39.488
You see something?

45:40.781 --> 45:41.823
No.

45:44.076 --> 45:45.827
What are you doing?

45:50.040 --> 45:51.541
Seeking power.

45:54.086 --> 45:55.337
Me, too.

45:59.216 --> 46:02.219
You feel like a leaf at the
mercy of the wind, don't you?

46:02.844 --> 46:06.515
Yep. That's right.
That's me.

46:08.100 --> 46:10.644
Since the day you were born,
one way or another,

46:10.727 --> 46:12.938
someone has been doing
something to you.

46:17.150 --> 46:19.945
No, I don't...
I don't think that's true.

46:20.028 --> 46:23.073
They've been doing something
to you against your will.

46:23.532 --> 46:25.617
And by now,
you're feeling helpless,

46:25.701 --> 46:27.703
like a leaf in the wind.

46:35.794 --> 46:38.422
Taylor, it would
help me out a lot

46:38.505 --> 46:39.923
if you'd just say
what's on your mind

46:40.007 --> 46:41.425
so I could understand you.

46:42.801 --> 46:44.553
You understand me.

46:47.556 --> 46:50.225
No matter how much you like
to feel sorry for yourself,

46:52.144 --> 46:54.104
you have to change that.

46:55.731 --> 46:57.232
I'm a warrior.

46:59.067 --> 47:01.987
A warrior would rather
be defeated and die

47:02.070 --> 47:04.197
than act against his nature.

47:07.075 --> 47:09.286
That is the path
you've chosen to take,

47:10.162 --> 47:12.205
whether you know it or not.

47:14.291 --> 47:16.918
You should assume
full responsibility.

47:19.004 --> 47:20.922
Responsibility for what?

47:21.256 --> 47:23.050
Responsibility for everything.

47:23.842 --> 47:25.844
Everything in your world.

47:31.391 --> 47:32.809
Come on, Robbie.

47:38.648 --> 47:40.525
Robbie, you're supposed
to clean your braces

47:40.609 --> 47:42.110
and come downstairs now.

47:42.194 --> 47:44.446
Shut up, jerko!
I'm doing it, okay?

47:44.529 --> 47:46.281
Don't "okay" me!

47:46.448 --> 47:47.824
You're a pest, you know that?

48:11.181 --> 48:12.307
Don't do that.

48:12.391 --> 48:14.017
I didn't do anything.

48:14.101 --> 48:15.644
You're such an infant.

48:26.822 --> 48:27.781
Ready?
Mmm-hmm.

48:27.864 --> 48:28.907
Where's Robbie?

48:28.990 --> 48:30.784
He says he's coming.

48:30.867 --> 48:31.910
Okay.

48:31.993 --> 48:33.620
Kiss Katrina, too.

48:34.162 --> 48:35.622
Good night, girls.
Good night.

48:35.705 --> 48:37.165
Rob, come on!

48:38.291 --> 48:40.001
Good night, sweetie.
Good night, Daddy.

48:41.294 --> 48:42.671
Ooh! The telephone.

48:43.505 --> 48:44.673
Hello?

48:45.173 --> 48:46.258
Yes.

48:47.175 --> 48:48.260
Okay.

48:48.343 --> 48:50.387
Dad, it's for you.
Oh.

48:50.470 --> 48:52.222
Oh, maybe it's
the insurance company.

48:53.348 --> 48:54.683
With good news.

48:58.395 --> 48:59.521
Hello?

49:02.607 --> 49:03.692
<i>Die!</i>

49:12.200 --> 49:13.952
Mom!

49:14.035 --> 49:15.036
Mom!

49:15.120 --> 49:16.413
Oh, my God!

49:16.496 --> 49:17.664
Stay here, baby.

49:17.747 --> 49:18.999
Robbie!

49:20.333 --> 49:21.877
We're coming, Robbie!

49:23.587 --> 49:24.629
Rob!

49:26.089 --> 49:27.299
Robbie!

49:31.219 --> 49:32.804
Dad, help me!

49:32.888 --> 49:33.972
Robbie!

49:34.473 --> 49:37.100
Taylor! Help us!

49:37.184 --> 49:38.393
Taylor!

49:39.311 --> 49:40.395
Please!

49:43.315 --> 49:45.317
Help! Taylor!

49:46.067 --> 49:47.277
Taylor!

49:48.737 --> 49:50.322
Hold tight, Robbie!

49:52.657 --> 49:53.909
The plug!

49:55.076 --> 49:56.411
No!

50:10.800 --> 50:11.885
Get out!

50:16.515 --> 50:17.849
Taylor!

50:17.933 --> 50:19.601
Taylor, where the hell were you?

50:20.060 --> 50:23.647
We're not safe here anymore. My
son almost dies and you sit here!

50:23.730 --> 50:25.690
I was protecting Carol Anne.

50:25.774 --> 50:30.904
It's her he's after,
not Robbie, not you or Diane.

50:34.115 --> 50:35.450
Carol Anne.

50:38.411 --> 50:41.414
Why the hell
won't you leave us alone?

50:44.626 --> 50:46.253
- Dad!
- Steven!

50:47.170 --> 50:51.466
<i>You can't keep her!
I am not dead!</i>

51:42.517 --> 51:43.893
He's still here.

51:46.104 --> 51:47.897
He feels she belongs to him.

51:48.481 --> 51:49.691
But why?

51:50.191 --> 51:51.443
I'm not sure,

51:51.776 --> 51:53.862
but he's used to getting
what he wants.

51:55.030 --> 51:56.281
Taylor.

51:57.490 --> 51:58.658
Who is he?

51:59.701 --> 52:00.869
What is he?

52:01.036 --> 52:03.204
He's a man filled with a demon,

52:03.705 --> 52:06.541
lost in a dimension
that surrounds our world.

52:07.959 --> 52:11.588
This entity believes that his
world and ours are the same.

52:12.672 --> 52:14.674
Why doesn't he know he's dead?

52:14.966 --> 52:16.092
Because he isn't.

52:18.053 --> 52:19.304
How can that be?

52:19.387 --> 52:21.181
Nothing really dies.

52:23.224 --> 52:25.894
Like a caterpillar
becomes a butterfly,

52:26.686 --> 52:30.106
death only transforms us
into another state of being.

52:31.733 --> 52:33.401
This man was evil

52:34.903 --> 52:37.113
and his soul remains evil

52:37.197 --> 52:39.824
because he chooses
not to see the light

52:39.908 --> 52:42.452
and pass on
to a different consciousness.

52:46.539 --> 52:48.208
How are we going
to fight this thing?

52:48.458 --> 52:50.251
Until we learn
how to defeat him,

52:51.920 --> 52:53.588
we do not let him win.

52:54.005 --> 52:55.882
That's a hell of a plan.
That's a lot of crap.

52:55.965 --> 52:57.258
I suppose you have
a plan of your own.

52:57.342 --> 52:58.677
That's a lot of crap!
Shh.

52:59.427 --> 53:01.846
Listen.
Don't come apart now.

53:04.974 --> 53:06.685
This spirit
is very clever.

53:07.686 --> 53:09.938
He knows your strength
is your love,

53:10.230 --> 53:11.856
and he hates you for that.

53:13.066 --> 53:15.402
He's been trying to pull
this family apart,

53:16.152 --> 53:18.154
and he will continue to try.

53:20.407 --> 53:21.908
If he succeeds,

53:21.991 --> 53:24.119
he will possess Carol Anne

53:25.245 --> 53:26.663
and destroy your spirit.

54:55.293 --> 54:56.836
Hi!

54:56.920 --> 54:58.129
Tangina!

54:58.213 --> 54:59.881
Hi, Diane.

54:59.964 --> 55:01.591
What are you doing here?

55:01.674 --> 55:05.345
Sorry to come unannounced, sweetie,
but I need to speak with you.

55:05.428 --> 55:06.805
Oh, I'm glad to see you.

55:06.888 --> 55:10.475
Oh, good. 'Cause we're
running out of time.

55:10.558 --> 55:13.436
Mmm-hmm,
below the old cemetery,

55:14.062 --> 55:17.065
what seems to be a tomb
with many bodies in it,

55:17.899 --> 55:20.568
directly below your house.

55:21.736 --> 55:23.112
Who are they?

55:23.196 --> 55:26.366
The researchers don't know
who these people were.

55:26.825 --> 55:28.910
There are no marked graves.

55:29.911 --> 55:33.164
There are, however, records
of a religious sect

55:33.248 --> 55:35.250
that mysteriously disappeared.

55:37.627 --> 55:39.003
What happened?

55:39.087 --> 55:41.381
Their spiritual leader
was a medium

55:41.464 --> 55:44.175
who led his followers
out to California

55:44.259 --> 55:48.137
in the early 1800s
to start a utopian society.

55:49.389 --> 55:52.225
They disappeared
near Cuesta Verde

55:53.434 --> 55:58.273
and were believed
massacred by Indians.

55:59.941 --> 56:01.609
This could be them.

56:12.287 --> 56:13.621
This funny?

56:17.500 --> 56:19.043
Well, no, uh...

56:20.044 --> 56:21.087
I love the health club,
you know.

56:21.170 --> 56:23.590
I'm just wondering when I
get the key to my locker?

56:26.259 --> 56:28.428
Sense of humor is good.

56:30.930 --> 56:32.891
You're going to need it.

57:26.069 --> 57:29.697
The entity has revealed
his essence to you, his enemy.

57:32.033 --> 57:35.995
Now that you've seen each
other, there'll be no mistakes.

57:37.246 --> 57:38.873
Take this smoke.

57:48.049 --> 57:49.217
Smoke,

57:50.426 --> 57:53.054
make him one with power
and knowledge.

57:55.348 --> 57:57.684
Here is a photo of those people.

57:58.434 --> 58:00.353
I think you should
have a look at it.

58:02.647 --> 58:04.732
I know this is
hard for you, dear,

58:05.400 --> 58:08.194
but I need your
verification on something.

58:09.737 --> 58:13.032
You see, I don't really trust

58:13.116 --> 58:15.743
my instincts anymore.

58:18.246 --> 58:20.957
Now, hold this one

58:22.250 --> 58:24.252
and tell me what you feel.

58:29.465 --> 58:31.050
Oh, my God, I've seen him!

58:31.342 --> 58:32.885
I thought so.
Where?

58:32.969 --> 58:36.764
Oh, my God. Here!
At the mall! At our house!

58:37.223 --> 58:38.307
Who is he?

58:38.391 --> 58:40.893
Tell me what you feel.
Just tell me what you feel.

58:40.977 --> 58:42.854
What do you want me to do?
Who is he?

58:42.937 --> 58:44.355
I've consulted others.

58:44.439 --> 58:47.233
They've told me things,
but they said you know more!

58:47.316 --> 58:48.776
I don't know anything!

58:48.860 --> 58:50.319
Yes, you do!

58:51.029 --> 58:52.363
You traveled to a dimension

58:52.447 --> 58:54.782
few people have ever
traveled to incarnate!

58:55.783 --> 58:58.286
Your daughter is
highly clairvoyant!

58:59.037 --> 59:01.289
As was your mother, I suspect

59:01.789 --> 59:03.791
As you are as well!

59:04.500 --> 59:06.878
Now tell me what you feel!

59:12.633 --> 59:14.594
It is him.
It's the preacher.

59:16.137 --> 59:18.848
They're following him in death
like they did in life.

59:20.058 --> 59:21.684
<i>They seal themselves
in the cavern,</i>

59:21.768 --> 59:24.479
<i>because Kane tells them the
end of the world is coming.</i>

59:26.689 --> 59:30.401
Come with me!

59:30.485 --> 59:33.404
<i>The day he predicts
for the end comes and goes,</i>

59:34.155 --> 59:36.574
<i>but Kane won't let them leave!</i>

59:36.657 --> 59:39.994
Don't! No, please!
Please don't!

59:40.745 --> 59:42.872
Please don't!

59:46.584 --> 59:47.835
Please...

59:47.960 --> 59:49.295
Oh, Diane.

59:50.880 --> 59:53.966
Yes, it all makes sense now.

59:54.842 --> 59:57.929
When you brought Carol
Anne back to this world,

59:59.055 --> 01:00:01.224
his followers became restless

01:00:01.349 --> 01:00:04.685
because they had tasted
the light of her being,

01:00:04.769 --> 01:00:06.562
her life force.

01:00:08.147 --> 01:00:09.857
Now he wants her back.

01:00:11.651 --> 01:00:14.862
This person is no longer human.

01:00:17.448 --> 01:00:19.033
He is the beast.

01:00:19.951 --> 01:00:25.039
<i>Earthly thoughts be silent now</i>

01:00:26.040 --> 01:00:28.876
<i>While with reverence...</i>

01:00:29.377 --> 01:00:31.754
You must take your family
back to Cuesta Verde.

01:00:34.507 --> 01:00:35.591
What?

01:00:36.759 --> 01:00:38.845
The evil spirit
that is stalking you,

01:00:39.554 --> 01:00:41.180
it knows who you are,

01:00:41.389 --> 01:00:43.808
where you are, how to find you,

01:00:44.976 --> 01:00:46.644
what your weaknesses are.

01:00:46.978 --> 01:00:48.855
Your best bet is
to confront him,

01:00:49.063 --> 01:00:51.274
surprise him on his own ground.

01:00:52.817 --> 01:00:55.611
But, Taylor, what about Diane
and the kids?

01:00:56.320 --> 01:00:58.072
They are your power

01:00:59.240 --> 01:01:00.950
and you are theirs.

01:01:21.095 --> 01:01:23.514
Uh, are things
desperate, Taylor?

01:01:25.224 --> 01:01:28.728
What you see as desperate,
I see as inevitable.

01:01:30.646 --> 01:01:32.440
I've done all I can.

01:01:33.524 --> 01:01:34.942
I must be leaving you now.

01:01:39.447 --> 01:01:40.865
I'll take you home.

01:01:41.449 --> 01:01:43.034
Um, guys,

01:01:43.743 --> 01:01:45.620
you know, there's, uh,
no reason to get depressed.

01:01:45.703 --> 01:01:47.830
I mean, Taylor's not here.
That's all right.

01:01:47.914 --> 01:01:51.667
We'll just keep on going just like we've
been doing, as a family, as a unit...

01:01:53.419 --> 01:01:56.714
Son, you know, I've told you
about the helmet and eating...

01:01:57.298 --> 01:01:58.799
I told you, I'm not hungry.

01:01:59.926 --> 01:02:01.344
Miniature golf.

01:02:01.636 --> 01:02:03.721
Tomorrow we can play
some miniature golf!

01:02:04.096 --> 01:02:05.640
We can get our putters...

01:02:07.099 --> 01:02:08.935
How about bowling, huh?

01:02:09.477 --> 01:02:11.145
You like bowling, sweet pea.

01:02:12.188 --> 01:02:14.440
Nature hike, Rob.
Huh? We'll get...

01:02:14.941 --> 01:02:16.317
Brisk walk?

01:02:17.652 --> 01:02:19.403
I know.
The water slide, huh?

01:02:19.612 --> 01:02:22.949
We'll take E. Buzz, we'll put water
wings on him, we'll shove him down,

01:02:23.157 --> 01:02:25.284
and laugh, won't we?

01:03:11.330 --> 01:03:13.833
So, after
Alice fell down the hole,

01:03:13.916 --> 01:03:15.626
Why'd she drink
from that bottle?

01:03:15.710 --> 01:03:17.795
Because it said
"drink me" on it.

01:03:18.045 --> 01:03:20.589
Oh. Were they going
to capture her

01:03:21.090 --> 01:03:22.633
and take her someplace bad?

01:03:23.467 --> 01:03:25.886
Yes, but Alice
gets home all right, remember?

01:03:27.680 --> 01:03:30.182
Did she know why they
wanted to hurt her?

01:03:30.808 --> 01:03:32.393
I don't think so, honey.

01:03:34.395 --> 01:03:35.896
'Cause I know.

01:03:36.564 --> 01:03:37.732
You know what?

01:03:38.149 --> 01:03:39.775
Why they're here.

01:03:42.069 --> 01:03:44.822
Why, baby?
Why are they here?

01:03:45.823 --> 01:03:48.159
Because they don't know
where else to go.

01:04:24.278 --> 01:04:26.238
God! Oh!

01:04:31.619 --> 01:04:32.912
God!

01:04:53.140 --> 01:04:57.436
<i>God is in his holy temple</i>

01:04:58.437 --> 01:05:03.192
<i>God is in his holy temple</i>

01:05:36.183 --> 01:05:37.518
Hi, angel!

01:05:46.026 --> 01:05:47.653
Are you okay, Dad?

01:05:48.195 --> 01:05:49.280
Yeah.

01:05:50.030 --> 01:05:52.783
I just want to
give my little girl a hug.

01:05:54.702 --> 01:05:55.786
Oh!

01:05:55.870 --> 01:05:59.373
Hey, your mom and I
would like to talk alone.

01:06:01.375 --> 01:06:03.586
Go put on your nightie, honey.

01:06:07.631 --> 01:06:09.258
What's going on, Steve?

01:06:12.428 --> 01:06:14.221
Nothing. I just
want us to be alone.

01:06:14.680 --> 01:06:16.390
Carol Anne's upset.

01:06:18.225 --> 01:06:19.477
Does that feel good?

01:06:19.560 --> 01:06:21.270
I should dry her hair.

01:06:21.562 --> 01:06:23.355
She's all right.
She's safe.

01:06:23.689 --> 01:06:25.024
Steven, come on!

01:06:27.234 --> 01:06:28.277
Honey!

01:06:28.360 --> 01:06:30.029
Is that good?
Honey!

01:06:30.571 --> 01:06:32.281
Don't! Not now!

01:06:32.364 --> 01:06:33.741
Why? When?

01:06:34.074 --> 01:06:35.326
What do you mean?

01:06:35.409 --> 01:06:37.203
Diane, I have needs, too!

01:06:37.495 --> 01:06:40.915
It seems to me, your needs have been
fulfilled by the bottle tonight!

01:06:49.381 --> 01:06:50.591
Oh!

01:06:51.091 --> 01:06:52.384
Steven, don't.

01:06:52.468 --> 01:06:56.430
Diane, are you accusing
me of being drunk?

01:06:56.514 --> 01:06:58.057
I'm not accusing you
of anything.

01:06:58.140 --> 01:06:59.767
Yes, you are, but that's
what you're thinking.

01:06:59.850 --> 01:07:01.101
No, I'm not! Yes, that's
what you're thinking.

01:07:01.185 --> 01:07:03.395
I know you! That's
what you're thinking!

01:07:05.606 --> 01:07:06.857
Spare me, Steven.

01:07:06.941 --> 01:07:10.444
Diane, you remember,
just the other day,

01:07:11.570 --> 01:07:14.532
when you were seven and you
were helping your mommy

01:07:14.615 --> 01:07:17.117
plant flowers in the garden?

01:07:19.286 --> 01:07:20.996
You saw it clearly!

01:07:21.330 --> 01:07:22.915
How the hell do you know that?

01:07:23.165 --> 01:07:25.292
'Cause I am smart.

01:07:25.960 --> 01:07:29.588
Oh, Mommy Jess...
Don't cry.

01:07:29.672 --> 01:07:31.882
Mommy Jess,
don't pout. No!

01:07:31.966 --> 01:07:33.968
You think that all
of our troubles

01:07:34.051 --> 01:07:36.053
are because of Carol Anne!

01:07:36.637 --> 01:07:38.556
You wish Carol Anne

01:07:38.639 --> 01:07:40.933
had never been given birth to!
No!

01:07:44.311 --> 01:07:48.023
You never wanted Carol Anne!

01:07:48.107 --> 01:07:49.400
Shh!

01:07:49.483 --> 01:07:51.569
But you thought it!
You thought it!

01:07:51.694 --> 01:07:53.445
You thought it, you thought it, baby!
No!

01:07:53.529 --> 01:07:54.697
Shh.

01:07:55.114 --> 01:07:56.532
You thought about it!

01:07:58.200 --> 01:08:00.828
You thought that?
You thought it! Shh!

01:08:02.204 --> 01:08:03.747
You thought it!

01:08:07.876 --> 01:08:08.919
Diane's had secrets!

01:08:09.837 --> 01:08:11.255
No, don't!
Diane!

01:08:11.380 --> 01:08:13.007
Don't! Don't touch me!

01:08:13.048 --> 01:08:14.758
Steven!

01:08:14.842 --> 01:08:17.303
I know you! I feel you!

01:08:17.386 --> 01:08:21.180
What is wrong with you?
What is happening to you?

01:08:22.474 --> 01:08:24.768
Why are you doing this?

01:08:24.852 --> 01:08:26.854
What is happening to you?

01:08:28.147 --> 01:08:30.189
Steven, stop it!

01:08:31.859 --> 01:08:33.068
Stop it!

01:08:33.152 --> 01:08:36.654
We want the angel!
The sweet pea!

01:08:36.738 --> 01:08:38.616
Stop it, stop it!

01:08:41.702 --> 01:08:43.120
No! Stop it!

01:08:45.538 --> 01:08:48.082
I love you! Damn you!

01:08:48.459 --> 01:08:51.754
He is in his holy temple!

01:08:53.671 --> 01:08:56.383
Don't you know that?
I love you!

01:08:56.466 --> 01:08:58.385
Believe me, I love you!

01:09:03.557 --> 01:09:05.434
Oh, God, leave me alone!

01:09:06.393 --> 01:09:09.897
What is it?
What's happening to you?

01:09:13.149 --> 01:09:14.234
What's going on?

01:09:14.318 --> 01:09:16.569
Leave me alone.
Leave me alone.

01:09:17.071 --> 01:09:19.073
What is it?
God, please!

01:09:19.156 --> 01:09:20.491
What's the matter?

01:09:20.573 --> 01:09:21.658
Oh, God!

01:09:21.742 --> 01:09:23.452
Steven...
God!

01:09:23.535 --> 01:09:25.621
Steven, what is it?
What's the matter?

01:09:28.582 --> 01:09:32.127
What is it? What is it, Steven?
Oh, God!

01:09:32.211 --> 01:09:33.587
What is it?

01:09:37.925 --> 01:09:39.176
Oh, God!

01:09:57.945 --> 01:09:59.405
Honey! Steven!

01:09:59.613 --> 01:10:01.448
Wake up! Wake up!

01:10:07.413 --> 01:10:09.164
Wake up! Wake up!

01:10:38.485 --> 01:10:39.695
Robbie!

01:10:39.778 --> 01:10:41.488
Robbie!
Carol Anne!

01:11:13.645 --> 01:11:15.355
Kids, where are you?

01:11:16.064 --> 01:11:18.025
Stay put!
We'll find you!

01:11:31.079 --> 01:11:32.289
Babies?

01:12:08.867 --> 01:12:12.037
Daddy, help me!
Help me, please!

01:12:12.120 --> 01:12:16.583
Dad!
Help me, Mom! Dad!

01:12:19.253 --> 01:12:20.504
No! No!

01:12:21.922 --> 01:12:24.967
Oh, Steven! No!

01:12:26.385 --> 01:12:27.594
Steven!

01:12:30.597 --> 01:12:31.807
No! No!

01:12:49.741 --> 01:12:51.368
Oh, God!

01:13:01.461 --> 01:13:02.629
Oh, honey.

01:13:05.632 --> 01:13:07.634
Carol Anne! Robbie!
Robbie!

01:13:17.728 --> 01:13:19.396
I'll check in here.
All right?

01:13:19.479 --> 01:13:20.480
Yeah.

01:13:23.650 --> 01:13:24.818
Robbie?

01:13:24.902 --> 01:13:26.278
Carol Anne?

01:13:26.904 --> 01:13:29.323
Oh, babies,
please answer me! Please!

01:13:44.129 --> 01:13:45.505
Are you in here?

01:13:48.216 --> 01:13:50.177
Kids! Kids, please come!

01:13:54.264 --> 01:13:56.308
Robbie! Carol Anne!

01:14:00.020 --> 01:14:01.104
Kids?

01:14:16.954 --> 01:14:18.163
Robbie!

01:14:20.707 --> 01:14:22.376
Carol Anne! Please!

01:14:25.837 --> 01:14:26.838
Mom!

01:14:28.715 --> 01:14:30.550
Oh, baby, baby,
are you all right?

01:14:32.886 --> 01:14:33.929
Diane?

01:14:35.263 --> 01:14:36.473
Where's Carol Anne?

01:14:36.556 --> 01:14:38.475
We can't find her.
I don't know.

01:14:38.558 --> 01:14:39.893
The garage!

01:14:40.769 --> 01:14:42.062
Carol Anne!

01:14:42.145 --> 01:14:43.146
Carol Anne!

01:14:43.230 --> 01:14:44.940
Baby, where are you?

01:14:46.108 --> 01:14:47.484
Carol Anne!

01:14:48.694 --> 01:14:50.070
Carol Anne!

01:14:51.238 --> 01:14:52.447
Carol Anne!
Carol Anne!

01:14:52.531 --> 01:14:53.740
Where are you?

01:14:54.074 --> 01:14:55.242
Honey?

01:14:55.742 --> 01:14:57.077
Oh, God.

01:14:57.160 --> 01:14:58.912
Carol Anne, open
the door, sweet pea!

01:14:58.996 --> 01:15:00.038
Oh, baby!

01:15:00.122 --> 01:15:01.748
Come on, honey, open the door!

01:15:01.832 --> 01:15:03.500
Lift up the knob, sweetheart.

01:15:03.583 --> 01:15:04.668
Come on honey, open the...

01:15:04.751 --> 01:15:05.836
What is it?

01:15:05.919 --> 01:15:08.213
Oh, sweetheart, that wasn't
Daddy upstairs in the bathroom.

01:15:08.296 --> 01:15:09.297
You know that!

01:15:09.423 --> 01:15:10.841
Oh, baby!

01:15:11.508 --> 01:15:12.759
What happened?
Jesus!

01:15:13.760 --> 01:15:15.012
Mom!

01:15:17.097 --> 01:15:18.098
Mom!

01:15:18.765 --> 01:15:20.308
- Dad, watch out!
- Look out!

01:15:20.892 --> 01:15:21.977
Mom!

01:15:22.060 --> 01:15:24.229
Okay, Diane, get in the car!

01:15:24.771 --> 01:15:26.106
Go, go, baby, 90!

01:15:26.148 --> 01:15:27.858
- Open the door, Carol Anne.
- Open the door!

01:15:27.941 --> 01:15:29.067
Open the door!

01:15:32.446 --> 01:15:34.072
Steven, come on!

01:15:34.156 --> 01:15:35.615
Daddy, hurry!

01:15:36.116 --> 01:15:37.284
Hurry!

01:15:37.784 --> 01:15:38.952
Go! Go!

01:15:41.621 --> 01:15:43.081
Get us out of here! Go!

01:15:43.165 --> 01:15:44.624
Dad, E. Buzz!

01:15:45.625 --> 01:15:47.252
E. Buzz, get in!

01:15:47.377 --> 01:15:48.545
- Come on, E. Buzz.
- E. Buzz!

01:15:48.628 --> 01:15:50.589
Come on, E. Buzz, get in!
Be a good boy!

01:15:50.672 --> 01:15:51.882
Come on, E. Buzz, get in.

01:15:51.965 --> 01:15:53.383
Come on, E. Buzz!

01:15:53.467 --> 01:15:55.093
Come on, E. Buzz! Get in!

01:15:56.553 --> 01:15:57.763
Come on, Robbie!

01:15:57.846 --> 01:15:58.972
Close the door!

01:16:00.182 --> 01:16:01.475
Dad,
let's get out of here!

01:16:01.558 --> 01:16:02.559
Come on.

01:16:05.604 --> 01:16:06.605
Come on, move!

01:16:06.688 --> 01:16:07.898
- Go!
- It won't move!

01:16:07.981 --> 01:16:09.107
Go!

01:16:09.191 --> 01:16:10.650
It won't start!

01:16:16.448 --> 01:16:17.991
Steven!
Go! Please!

01:16:26.208 --> 01:16:27.417
No! No!

01:16:28.502 --> 01:16:29.836
Look out!

01:16:39.262 --> 01:16:40.680
Move, damn it! Move!

01:16:48.105 --> 01:16:49.731
Get going, Steven!

01:16:51.066 --> 01:16:52.234
Hurry!

01:16:59.866 --> 01:17:00.992
Drive the car!

01:17:01.076 --> 01:17:02.619
Now, move! Move!

01:17:21.888 --> 01:17:23.098
Oh, Jesus!

01:17:50.125 --> 01:17:52.335
We're going back to
Cuesta Verde, aren't we?

01:17:55.088 --> 01:17:56.464
That's right.

01:17:57.299 --> 01:17:58.884
But what about the kids?

01:18:01.595 --> 01:18:03.430
Taylor said we go back
as a family.

01:18:03.513 --> 01:18:05.515
We go back together.
That's all of us.

01:18:07.017 --> 01:18:08.935
Do you believe him, Dad?

01:18:14.774 --> 01:18:16.193
Honey, it was real smart of you

01:18:16.276 --> 01:18:18.111
to hide in the car like that.

01:18:18.195 --> 01:18:19.654
It wasn't my idea.

01:18:19.988 --> 01:18:22.157
Taylor said it was
